  "texts": [
    "First, the glarepoint shadowgraphy images are processed using a convolutional hourglass network [63], which extracts pixel-aligned features I i from the input images at the location x, y on the image plane (orange blocks).",
    "This operation is performed simultaneously for a sequence of N = 5 images, with the snapshot considered for reconstruction in the middle of the sequence.",
    "In the temporal fusion network, temporal correlations between the spatial pixel-aligned features I i are extracted through 1Dconvolutional operations.",
    "The extracted spatio-temporal features F i (last blue block), along with their corresponding spatial coordinates x, y, are forwarded to the MLP.",
    "To preserve sharp spatial information of the considered time step, the pixelaligned features from the central image are directly forwarded to the MLP as well."
  ],
